-- Chinese Ambassador to Japan Urges Dialogue to Improve Ties, Nikkei Says
-- B y   T a k   K u m a k u r a
-- 2010-11-08T22:26:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-08/chinese-ambassador-to-japan-urges-dialogue-to-improve-ties-nikkei-says.html
China and Japan should hold talks to
improve relations strained after the September collision between
a Chinese trawler and Japanese Coast Guard vessels, the Chinese
ambassador to Japan, Cheng Yonghua, told the Nikkei newspaper in
an interview.   The collision took place near disputed islands known as
Senkaku in Japan and Diaoyu in China. While reiterating that the
islands belong to China, Yonghua said the countries should
resolve the issue through dialogue, according to report.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Takehiko Kumakura at 
 tkumakura@bloomberg.net  